@danny0405 : Agree with @vinothchandar  in what this change would accomplish. If we have incremental syncing enabled and move timeline server hosting to Job Manager, we will get the full benefit of storage RPC call reductions here.  

With this change, the reusability  is limited to tasks running within a Task Manager at the scope of a single Hudi commit. For the next Hudi commit, a full resync of file-system view will happen. 

Now for the incremental timeline sync, we definitely need to enable this but we need to see if this [issue](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HUDI-1275)  is still present in master  using a  long running job and get to the root cause.

